The '''gravitic amplitude modulator''' or '''GAM''', also known as a '''gravitic wave modulator''' or simply '''gravitic modulator''', was a device created by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] to allow a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] to modulate [[Gravity/Legends|gravity]] in its immediate area.

[[Danni Quee]] and [[Cilghal]] developed a modified modulator on [[Eclipse Station]] in [[27 ABY/Legends|27 ABY]], as part of [[Yammosk Action]]. A more complex and sophisticated version of the [[Gravity well projector/Legends|gravity well projector]] employed on [[Immobilizer 418 Interdictor-class Heavy Cruiser|Immobilizer 418]] interdictors, it allowed the jamming of [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[yammosk]]s. The device would emit gravitic pulses capable of interfering with those generated by a yammosk, thus effectively jamming the creature's transmissions. The resulting confusion from losing this "hive mind" amongst Yuuzhan Vong [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] and/or warriors caused once tight formations and tactics to decompose into loose clusters fighting entirely independent from the remainder of their forces.

The first GAM was installed aboard the ''[[Errant Venture/Legends|Errant Venture]]'' for use at the end of the [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|Battle of Coruscant]]. The [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] later installed one on the [[Imperial Remnant]] Star Destroyer [[Defiant (Imperial-class)|''Defiant'']]. Gravitic modulators were used on the [[StealthX]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] which was designed to defeat [[mass-detector]]s. This aided the craft in remaining undetected by enemy [[Sensor/Legends|sensors]]. On a StealthX it replaced the third [[Proton torpedo/Legends|proton torpedo]] launcher.

